<paragraph id="8BD3FC2E512DFFEFFF3A233DFEF4FACA" blockId="9.[144,265,1373,1397]" box="[144,265,1373,1397]" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B918203C512DFFEFFF3A233DFEF4FACA" box="[144,265,1373,1397]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD3FC2E512DFFEFFF3A23E5FE34FA03" blockId="9.[144,1104,1413,1469]" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">
The specific name is derived from Latin 
<emphasis id="B918203C512DFFEFFDCB23E5FD4CFA22" box="[609,689,1413,1437]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">gracilis</emphasis>
+ 
<emphasis id="B918203C512DFFEFFD7E23E5FCEFFA22" box="[724,786,1413,1437]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">cornu</emphasis>
= slender + antenna, referring to its slender antennae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD3FC2E512DFFEFFF3A2398FF0EF9AF" blockId="9.[144,243,1528,1552]" box="[144,243,1528,1552]" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B918203C512DFFEFFF3A2398FF0EF9AF" box="[144,243,1528,1552]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD3FC2E512DFFEFFF3A207FFEB0F928" blockId="9.[144,1104,1567,1687]" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C87AD512DFFEFFE722040FDA4F987" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1891" box="[472,601,1568,1592]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Cyrebion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticorne">
<emphasis id="B918203C512DFFEFFE722040FDA4F987" box="[472,601,1568,1592]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">C. laticorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in body coloration, but differs in the slightly thickened antennae, narrower pronotum and different emargination of female abdominal sternite VIII. From 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C87AD512DFFEFFE452000FD45F9C7" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1995" box="[495,696,1632,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Themus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrufolineatus">
<emphasis id="B918203C512DFFEFFE452000FD45F9C7" box="[495,696,1632,1656]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="586">C. subrufolineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it can be easily distinguished by the body coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF13ACA6512EFFECFF7E2558FE58FC36" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207762" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5207762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5207762/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" startId="10.[212,279,824,846]" targetBox="[212,1172,175,794]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="8BD3FC2E512EFFECFF7E2558FE58FC36" blockId="10.[212,1172,824,905]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
Figure 3. Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C87AD512EFFECFE402558FCD8FCF1" authority="Fairmaire. Different" authorityName="Fairmaire. Different" authorityYear="1891" box="[490,805,824,846]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Cyrebion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B918203C512EFFECFE402558FDB8FCF1" box="[490,581,824,846]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Cyrebion</emphasis>
Fairmaire. Different
</taxonomicName>
localities of the three species are: 
<emphasis id="B918203C512EFFECFF7E2536FF15FCD3" bold="true" box="[212,232,854,876]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6C87AD512EFFECFF442536FDE4FCD4" authority="Fairmaire" authorityName="Fairmaire" box="[238,537,853,876]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Cyrebion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticornis">
<emphasis id="B918203C512EFFECFF442536FE56FCD3" box="[238,427,854,876]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Cyrebion laticornis</emphasis>
Fairmaire
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B918203C512EFFECFD892536FDCAFCD3" bold="true" box="[547,567,854,876]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Δ</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6C87AD512EFFECFD972536FC5CFCD4" authority="(Wittmer)" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Wittmer" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[573,929,853,876]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Cyrebion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrufolineatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B918203C512EFFECFD972536FCC8FCD3" box="[573,821,854,876]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Cyrebion subrufolineatus</emphasis>
(Wittmer)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22B9D47512EFFECFC0D2535FBE4FCD4" box="[935,1049,853,875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="B918203C512EFFECFBB42536FBCFFCD3" bold="true" box="[1054,1074,854,876]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">-</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6C87AD512EFFECFB922536FEB2FC36" authority="Yang &amp; Yang, 2010" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Cyrebion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilicornis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B918203C512EFFECFB922536FEB2FC36" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Cyrebion gracilicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22B9D47512EFFECFEFE2514FE58FC36" box="[340,421,884,905]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C376AFA5512EFFECFF7E2588FC48FB77" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD3FC2E512EFFECFF7E2588FDAAFBBF" blockId="10.[212,599,1000,1024]" box="[212,599,1000,1024]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="B918203C512EFFECFF7E2588FDAAFBBF" bold="true" box="[212,599,1000,1024]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C87AD512EFFECFED72588FDAAFBBF" authority="Fairmaire" authorityName="Fairmaire. Different" authorityYear="1891" box="[381,599,1000,1024]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Cyrebion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B918203C512EFFECFED72588FE1EFBBF" bold="true" box="[381,483,1000,1024]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Cyrebion</emphasis>
Fairmaire
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD3FC2E512EFFECFF7E2270FC48FB77" blockId="10.[212,1172,1040,1224]" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">
All of the known species are distributed in 
<collectingCountry id="F37BBCBE512EFFECFD7A2270FCE5FB97" box="[720,792,1040,1064]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">China</collectingCountry>
, where they are restricted to the south-western area (
<figureCitation id="1357E0AB512EFFECFE122250FDE7FBF7" box="[440,538,1072,1096]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="10.[212,279,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,175,794]" captionTargetId="figure-232@10.[212,1173,173,794]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution of Cyrebion Fairmaire. Different localities of the three species are: • Cyrebion laticornis Fairmaire, Δ Cyrebion subrufolineatus (Wittmer) comb. nov. - Cyrebion gracilicornis sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5207762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5207762/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). Judging from the current distribution pattern, we suppose that this genus may not be endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F37BBCBE512EFFECFD7D2230FCE2FBD7" box="[727,799,1104,1128]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">China</collectingCountry>
, instead, more unknown species should exist within the Oriental region, especially in the adjacent area of south-west 
<collectingCountry id="F37BBCBE512EFFECFF7E22F0FEE0FB17" box="[212,285,1168,1192]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="587">China</collectingCountry>
. We hope that this study will initiate the recognition of this genus, with more and more species discovered by extensive investigations in future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
